-- Summers Says Obama Tax Deal With Republicans Will Become Law by Christmas
-- B y   C h r i s t o p h e r   W e l l i s z
-- 2010-12-09T14:26:37Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-09/summers-says-obama-tax-deal-with-republicans-will-become-law-by-christmas.html
Lawrence Summers, President Barack
Obama’s top economic adviser, said he expects a deal to extend
Bush-era tax cuts will become law by Christmas.  Summers, director of the National Economic Council, told
CNBC today that the proposed legislation will give the U.S.
economy “a shot in the arm” by lowering the payroll tax and
extending unemployment benefits.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Chris Wellisz at 
 cwellisz@bloomberg.net  